      <div class="text">
        <h3>Problem</h3>
        <p>Bitcoin ATMs offer a convenient and easy to use physical platform for cryptocurrency users looking to
          purchase Bitcoin with cash. These kiosks serve a market that includes unbanked and underbanked individuals who
          either have no access to credit/debit cards, or simply do not believe in traditional banking. </p>
        <p>Providing these users with a simple, secure experience when conducting an ATM transaction is essential for
          Bitstop to secure return customers and build a brand that users can trust. The company’s ATMs, however, relied
          on outdated industry-standard hardware and software that interfered with a user’s experience and with
          Bitstop’s ability to differentiate its brand. The ATM touch screen was substandard, the UI cluttered and
          overwhelming, and the user experience confusing and lacking in transparency. Also, there was no means to
          update the existing software to add features to increase user engagement beyond conducting a transaction
          (e.g., integration with Bitstop’s mobile app, or experience surveys).</p>
        <p>The combination of these factors cascaded down into negative user reviews, an inability to build a franchise
          program effectively, and little brand differentiation from competitors.&nbsp;</p>
        <p></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

</section>

